<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1752,2032]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,153,323]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,420,1824,1851]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Whole fly as 
<figureCitation box="[577,674,1825,1851]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–129" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[190,1391,202,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 123–129. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 123, whole fly; 124, frons; 125, detail of frons; 126, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 127, side of thorax; 128, abdomen; 129, hypopygium. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573400/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 123</figureCitation>
. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[787,883,1825,1851]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–129" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[190,1391,202,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 123–129. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 123, whole fly; 124, frons; 125, detail of frons; 126, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 127, side of thorax; 128, abdomen; 129, hypopygium. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573400/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 124</figureCitation>
, largely devoid of microtrichia (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1345,1824,1851]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–129" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[190,1391,202,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 123–129. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 123, whole fly; 124, frons; 125, detail of frons; 126, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 127, side of thorax; 128, abdomen; 129, hypopygium. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573400/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
). Cheek with 3 bristles and jowl with a single longer and more robust bristle. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[347,444,1897,1923]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–129" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[190,1391,202,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 123–129. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 123, whole fly; 124, frons; 125, detail of frons; 126, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 127, side of thorax; 128, abdomen; 129, hypopygium. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573400/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 126</figureCitation>
, the labella without short spinules below. Thorax brown. Mesopleuron with hairs and a single long bristle, and with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1124,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–129" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[190,1391,202,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 123–129. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 123, whole fly; 124, frons; 125, detail of frons; 126, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 127, side of thorax; 128, abdomen; 129, hypopygium. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573400/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 127</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal as 
<figureCitation box="[864,960,1969,1995]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–129" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[190,1391,202,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 123–129. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 123, whole fly; 124, frons; 125, detail of frons; 126, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 127, side of thorax; 128, abdomen; 129, hypopygium. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573400/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 128</figureCitation>
. Venter brown, and with hairs on segments 5 and 6). Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[442,539,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–129" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[190,1391,202,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[168,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 123–129. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 123, whole fly; 124, frons; 125, detail of frons; 126, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 127, side of thorax; 128, abdomen; 129, hypopygium. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573400/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 129</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[575,621,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 130–135" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1468,1493]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,345,1443]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 130–135. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 130; hypandrium from below plus penis complex; 131, front tarsus; 132, front basitarsus; 133, hind femur; 134, wing and haltere; 135, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573402/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">130</figureCitation>
). Legs brown. Fore tarsus 
<figureCitation box="[918,1013,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 130–135" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1468,1493]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,345,1443]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 130–135. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 130; hypandrium from below plus penis complex; 131, front tarsus; 132, front basitarsus; 133, hind femur; 134, wing and haltere; 135, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573402/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 131</figureCitation>
, with some small spinules below the basitarsus (
<figureCitation box="[278,377,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 130–135" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1468,1493]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,345,1443]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 130–135. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 130; hypandrium from below plus penis complex; 131, front tarsus; 132, front basitarsus; 133, hind femur; 134, wing and haltere; 135, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573402/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 132</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.60 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur longer than those of anteroventral row (
<figureCitation box="[761,860,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 130–135" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1468,1493]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,345,1443]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 130–135. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 130; hypandrium from below plus penis complex; 131, front tarsus; 132, front basitarsus; 133, hind femur; 134, wing and haltere; 135, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573402/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 133</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with a dozen moderately differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1321,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 130–135" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1468,1493]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,345,1443]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 130–135. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 130; hypandrium from below plus penis complex; 131, front tarsus; 132, front basitarsus; 133, hind femur; 134, wing and haltere; 135, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573402/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 134 &amp; 135</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[1336,1437,225,251]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.39" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="1.39">1.39 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.45. Costal ratios 3.13: 1: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[1003,1103,261,287]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
long. Vein 3 without a hair. 2 unequal axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[664,764,297,323]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere brown (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1337,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 130–135" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1468,1493]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,345,1443]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 130–135. Megaselia ghalateshahensis n. sp. male. 130; hypandrium from below plus penis complex; 131, front tarsus; 132, front basitarsus; 133, hind femur; 134, wing and haltere; 135, base of wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573402/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 134</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
